{
  "texts": [
    "Line 18 -27 covers the standard DP iteration for a row (client).",
    "Finally, we perform a standard backtracing from the best cell (maximum aggregate value) to find the optimal subset of clients.",
    "Example Fig. 8 illustrates a simple example of mapping five clients to DNN m j.",
    "The DNN at batch size b j = 3 can satisfy the latency constraint of three clients, c1, c2 and c3.",
    "Whereas at batch size b j = 2, the DNN can satisfy two more clients, c4 and c5."
